      '## I\'m submitting a\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\n[x] Regression (a behavior that used to work and stopped working in a new release)\r\n[x] Bug report  <!-- Please search GitHub for a similar issue or PR before submitting -->\r\n[ ] Feature request\r\n[x] Documentation issue or request\r\n[ ] Support request => Please do not submit support request here, instead see https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#question\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n## Current behavior\r\n\r\nDynamically bootstraped angular doesn\'t use the routing like it should.\r\nWhen I change states the page gets reloaded. \r\nI try to set up server side rendering and use AOT compiled angular.\r\n\r\n## Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAngular should\'nt reload the page when you use an "a" tag with an "routerLink" attribute atleast.\r\n\r\n## Minimal reproduction of the problem with instructions\r\n\r\nHere is the current repo: https://gitlab.com/zmb-lab/Proof_of_Concept_for_SSR\r\n\r\nInstall the dependencies and run\r\n\r\n    $ gulp build\r\n\r\nYou need to remove my preventDefault event to see the default behaviour.\r\n   \r\n## What is the motivation / use case for changing the behavior?\r\nIf you use the angular-router components you should use the router instead of regular html navigation.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nAngular version: 4.3.6\r\n<!-- Check whether this is still an issue in the most recent Angular version -->\r\n\r\nFor Tooling issues:\r\n- Node version: 8.2.1  <!-- run `node --version` -->\r\n- Platform:macOS  <!-- Mac, Linux, Windows -->\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n'
