      '## I\'m submitting a...\r\n<pre><code>\r\n[ ] Regression (a behavior that used to work and stopped working in a new release)\r\n[x] Bug report  <!-- Please search GitHub for a similar issue or PR before submitting -->\r\n[ ] Feature request\r\n[ ] Documentation issue or request\r\n[ ] Support request => Please do not submit support request here, instead see https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#question\r\n</code></pre>\r\n\r\n## Current behavior\r\nWhen using animation, bound to a property, setting a transition of `* => *` to trigger every time the property changes, the animation does not trigger if the property is a list of the same length as before.\r\n\r\nKey points are :\r\nin list component :\r\n```typescript\r\n transition(\'* => *\', [ ... ] ) // from angular doc on stagger animation\r\n```\r\n```html\r\n<div [@listAnimation]="items">\r\n      <div *ngFor="let item of items">\r\n        {{ item.id }} - {{ item.name }}\r\n      </div>\r\n</div>\r\n```\r\nin main component :\r\n```html\r\n <my-list [items]="items | async"></my-list>\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected behavior\r\nThe animation should trigger every time the binding changes, as specified in the doc.\r\n\r\n## Minimal reproduction of the problem with instructions\r\nYou can find a plunker here :\r\nhttp://plnkr.co/edit/yL4mBLtnB4ovVf8axtl3?p=preview\r\nHow it works\r\n- The parent component gives a list to its child\r\n- The child displays the list items, applying an animation every time it receives a new list\r\n- [ERROR ->] When giving a list of same size, the animation does not trigger\r\n\r\nThis is the case with List from immutable, but also applies with a simple array.\r\n\r\nI do not know if it is the binding that does not wake up, if it is the async pipe, or something more related to the animation. It does work with a list of number though (instead of a list of object)\r\n\r\n\r\n## What is the motivation / use case for changing the behavior?\r\nI have an application with a master / details view. The master has a list. This list is paginated.\r\nI want to animate the item every time the user changes the page.\r\nI have an application with a master / details view. The master has a list of children. When the user chooses an item, the list shows its children (kind of a tree view). If same length of children, no animation.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n<pre><code>\r\nAngular version: 4.4.0-RC.0 but same thing with 4.3.6 (I updated to see if the problem was still present)\r\n\r\nBrowser:\r\n- Chrome (desktop) version 60\r\n\r\n</code></pre>\r\n'
